HEADWORD: Rusma
<hw>Rus"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupt. from Turk.
<ets>khyryzma</ets> a paste used as a depilatory, fr. Gr. <?/ an
unguent; cf. F. <ets>rusma</ets>.]</ety> <def>A depilatory made of
orpiment and quicklime, and used by the Turks. See
<er>Rhusma</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

